Weather was mostly cloudy- warm- humid- and breezy.  Typical wildlife spotted (sandhill cranes- wild turkeys- gray and red squirrels- rabbits- etc.).  Whitetail deer sightings not as numerous.
Partly cloudy.  0.9 inches of rain two nights previous.  Lake level on the low end of normal.

Cloudy- misty- and 60 degrees at 10:00 A.M. 06/06/2011. Cloudy- misty- and 60 degrees at 10:00 A.M. 06/06/2011. Air temperature at 70 degrees- partly cloudy skies- and slightly less humid.  Some milfoil spotted in the are of the Zebra Mussel Sampler but still seems under control at this date.  Assisted by Wolf Lake area resident Jim Anderson.  Partly cloudy skies on 7/12/11.  Air temperature at 70 degrees and somewhat less humid.  Some milfoil in the vacinity of the Zebra Mussel Sampler but still seems under contol on this date.  Assisted by Wolf Lake area resident Jim Anderson. Partly to mostly cloudy.  Some scattered light rain in the area.   Today's date is Saturday- August 13.  Weather is cloudy to mostly cloudy with light rain showers in the ares.  Surface water temperature at zebra mussel substrate site is 76.8 degrees.

Partly Cloudy and Breezy. New Zebra Mussel substrate location is approximately 100 ft. southeast of the public launch.  Weather conditions at first check of substrate on June 19 was sunny and hot.  Air temperature was 93 degrees and water temperature at substrate was 82.9 degrees.  Lake water level has dropped since initial placing of substrate on May 18 but still in the normal range.  Surrounding area in need of rain.   Zebra Mussel sampler first monitored on June 19.  Please note the very top of the sampler was above water because of drop in lake level.  Sampler was re-set below water line.  New sampler location is 100 ft southeast of the public launch.  Weather conditions on June 19 were sunny and hot.  Air temperature of 93 degrees. Zebra Mussel sampler checked 08/27/2012.  Having trouble keeping upper substrate submerged because of low lake water levels.  Sunny morning with a slight breeze.

Nice morning.  Partly cloudy with a slight breeze.  Lake level has dropped approximately 8 - 9 inches.  Removed Zebra Mussel substrate this mornong. Partly cloudy with a slight breeze.  Nice morning.  Zebra Mussel substrate removed from the lake this morning.
Sunny with a slight breeze.  Lake level still normal.
Cloudy with Northeast wind of approximately 10 mph.  No EWM control by chemical application this year.

Cloudy- humid- with wind from the southwest at 5 mph.  Lake level high.  Migratory songbirds in the area along w/ Sand Hill Cranes.  Panfish on spawning beds.  Air temp. at time of setting substrate is 79 degrees F. Partly cloudy with a variable breeze.  Lake level has dropped approximately 4" since last report.
Partly cloudy and breezy.  Wind out of the southeast at 10 mph.  Aquatic vegetation growth starting.  Fish are off the spawning beds.
Unseasonably cool and windy.  Partly cloudy skies.  Lake water level on the high side of normal.

Partly cloudy with a variable light breeze.  Lake water level has dropped about 4" since last report.  Upper portion of zebra mussel substrate sampler was "above water."  Adjusted sampler to below water level.

Mostly cloudy.  Air temperature at 65 degrees. Winds variable at 5-10 mph. Partly cloudy with southerly winds at 5-10 mph.   Partly cloudy with southerly winds at 5-10 mph.  Air temperature at time of monitoring was 80.6 degrees F.  Todays monitoring date is 7/11/2015.  Very hot and humid today (8/16/15).  Partly cloudy with southerly winds at 5-10 mph.  Lake level has dropped 4.5 inches since 7/11/15.  Surface water temp. at substrate site 85.2 degrees.   Sept. 29- 2015.- 10:00 A.M.  Breaking overcast this morning.  Cold front moved through last night with 2" of rain.

Partly cloudy and breezy.  Wind from the west at 15-20 mph.  Aproximately 0.5 inches of rain this morning.  Lake level up slightly since initial zebra mussel substrate setting on 5/11/15.  Most fish off spawning beds.  Wolf Lake was chemically treated for EWM on 5/27/15.
High clouds- warm and humid.  Air temperature at time of monitoring- 85.2 degrees.  Time of monitoring is 2:00 P.M.

column1: W089 degrees- 37.516' Partly Cloudy- warm and humid.  Light variable winds.

column2: Partly cloudy with 0 - 5mph wind from the east.  High clouds- warm and humid.  Lake level has dropped approximately 4 ".
Sunny- pleasant and breezy.  Accompanied by my wife Bev.

Sunny and pleasant- with a slight easterly breeze at 0 - 5 mph.  Panfish- including some largemouth bass- venturing into shallow water.  Lake is at a healthy level this year.  Good to see at this time of year.  Sandhill Crane nest close by with one chick and one unhatched egg.  Native songbirds preparing to nest.
Sunny- hot and humid.  Southerly breeze @ 0-5 mph.  Zebra mussel substrate location N43 degrees 47.805'- W089 degrees 37.513'.
